// ================== FIRMWARE v1.3.0 ==================
// Base:   v1.2.1 (all FIX-A…FIX-D + FIX-01…FIX-11 intact)
//
// NEW v1.3.0:
//
//   [ROLLBACK]  OTA boot validation + automatic rollback.
//               Before OTA reboot: NVS "boot_check" = "PENDING".
//               In FW_INIT: if PENDING, run FW_BOOT_VALIDATE state.
//               Validates: sensors OK + MQTT connects within 30 s.
//               Pass → write "OK", publish OTA_VALIDATED, → FW_ACTIVE.
//               Fail → Update.rollback(), publish OTA_ROLLBACK, restart.
//
//   [CHECKSUM]  SHA-256 validation of OTA binary before Update.end().
//               Update topic payload may carry optional "sha256" field.
//               If present: computed over written bytes, compared to field.
//               Mismatch → Update.abort(), OTA_FAIL reason CHECKSUM_MISMATCH.
//               Missing   → skip check, log warning, proceed (backward compat).
//               mbedtls/sha256.h used (bundled in ESP-IDF, no extra lib).
//
//   [SIM-NB]    simEnterSleep() and simWake() are now fully non-blocking.
//               Both send their AT command and return immediately.
//               handleSimOp() called every tick advances the timer and sets
//               simSleeping when the modem settle time has elapsed.
//               FW_SLEEP sub-states gate on simOpDone() before proceeding.
//               SIM_ENTER_SLEEP settle: 2000 ms  (unchanged duration, non-blocking).
//               SIM_WAKE        settle: 5000 ms  (unchanged duration, non-blocking).
//
//   [LTE-NB]    initLTE() blocking delays replaced with FW_LTE_INIT state machine.
//               Sub-states: LTE_AT, LTE_CPIN, LTE_CSQ, LTE_CREG (up to 20 retries),
//               LTE_CGATT, LTE_CGDCONT, LTE_CGACT, LTE_CGPADDR, LTE_PING, LTE_DONE.
//               Each sub-state fires its AT command and waits via millis() timer.
//               On completion → FW_ACTIVE. On registration failure → FW_ACTIVE
//               with lteReady=false (MQTT will retry independently).
//
//   [I2C-REC]   Automatic I2C bus recovery on consecutive NO_ACK faults.
//               recoverI2C(): bit-bangs up to 9 SCL pulses via pinMode/digitalWrite,
//               issues STOP condition, then calls Wire.begin() to reinitialise.
//               Triggered when inaFailCount or encFailCount reaches 2 consecutive
//               NO_ACK results on the 30s sensor check cycle.
//               After recovery: re-runs checkSensors(), publishes result.
//               If still failing: sets i2cFault=true, blocks startMotor(),
//               publishes I2C_RECOVERY_FAIL.
//               On next passing check: clears i2cFault, publishes I2C_RECOVERED.
//
// ALL FIX-01…FIX-11, FIX-A…FIX-D comments preserved verbatim.
// BUZZER: zero changes.
// =========================================================================




